@page "/getting-started"

<PageTitle>Getting Started</PageTitle>

<h1>Getting Started</h1>

<p>Use P4nda Tracker to record when something was taken, see when it is next due, and keep an eye on the stock you have left.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
    P4nda Tracker is a personal reminder and record-keeping tool. Always follow advice from your doctor, pharmacist, and product packaging.
</div>

<div class="alert alert-secondary" role="alert">
    Your tracking data stays on your device. There is no user account to create, and this app does not store your data on a server. If you want a backup or need to move to another device, export your data from <strong>Settings</strong>.
</div>

<div class="row g-3">
    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h5 class="mb-0">Example: tracking paracetamol</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol class="mb-3">
                    <li>Select <strong>+ Add New</strong> from the Home page.</li>
                    <li>Enter a <strong>Name</strong> such as <strong>Paracetamol 500 mg</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Set <strong>Default Stock Usage</strong> to <strong>2</strong> if you usually take two tablets.</li>
                    <li>Add limits for <strong>Qty 1, Hours 4</strong> and <strong>Qty 4, Hours 24</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Add a <strong>Stock Acquisition</strong> for the tablets you currently have available.</li>
                    <li>Select <strong>Save</strong>, then use <strong>Track Now</strong> whenever you take a dose.</li>
                </ol>

                <p class="mb-0 text-muted">The Home page will then show when it was last tracked, when it is next due, and how much stock remains, all using the data stored on this device.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h5 class="mb-0">What is good to track?</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>This app works best for items where timing, quantity, and stock matter.</p>

                <ul class="mb-0">
                    <li>Medicines with spacing rules, such as pain relief or cold and flu treatments.</li>
                    <li>Prescription doses where you want a clear history of what was taken and when.</li>
                    <li>Supplements or recurring treatments that you want to take on a consistent schedule.</li>
                    <li>Items where remaining stock matters, such as tablets, inhalers, sachets, or eye drops.</li>
                    <li>Anything with more than one limit, such as a short gap between doses and a daily cap.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h5 class="mb-0">Tips for using the software</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ul class="mb-0">
                    <li>Set a default stock usage so <strong>Track Now</strong> records your usual dose with one tap.</li>
                    <li>Add every limit that matters to you, for example both an every-4-hours rule and an every-24-hours rule.</li>
                    <li>Use the edit screen to correct times or quantities if you tracked something quickly and want to tidy it up later.</li>
                    <li>Record new packs in <strong>Stock Acquisitions</strong> so the stock total stays useful.</li>
                    <li>Mark regular items as favourites and switch to <strong>Grid View</strong> if you track several items at once.</li>
                    <li>Export your data from <strong>Settings</strong> before clearing browser data or moving to a new device, because your tracking history is stored locally on this device.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4 d-flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-secondary">
        <span class="bi bi-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></span> Back to Home
    </a>
    <a href="/settings" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">
        <span class="bi bi-gear" aria-hidden="true"></span> Open Settings
    </a>
</div>
